The paper discusses model compression for neural nets, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and data structures (cs.DS). Given that the paper specifically focuses on neural nets for object recognition, it is most likely to fall under cs.CV and cs.LG. However, since the paper presents a general framework for model compression that can be applied to various types of models, it could also be relevant to cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.DS.
